                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> <blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />Tell a rogue that he must obtain a dozen daggers in order to be balanced and see what he says. <br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />You hit the damn nail on the head.  Best analogy I've seen yet.<br /><br />But to complete that analogy the rogue would have to compete for those 12 daggers against all of but 3 classes in eq.  The fact that we have to compete with everyone from wis casters to hybrids to bards, hell, every class but warriors, monks and rogues, really eats at me.<br /><br />If I have to compete against <b>12 other classes</b> for spectral parchments then more than 2 should drop in an entire week of guildraids.<br /><br />edit:  <br /><br />Just some rough numbers:  I'd estimate we have about 50 classes on our raids who require spectral parchments.  I know it's more but lets work with that.  To be conservative lets say each class only needs 6 of them, 3 in 63 and 3 in 64.  6 is also low but lets go with it.<br /><br />That's <b>300</b> spectral parchments we need to equip everyone.  Last week we got roughly 6 off raid mobs.  That means in 50 weeks we can equip everyone.<br /><br />And that's being conservative in the amount we need and not even including dupes that will just sit in the guildbank.<br /><br />50 weeks.  Brilliant.  We could equip all our alts in Ssra gear in that amount of time.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
